            <div class="section-title">
                <h2>Ghana And Video Games</h2>
                <p>Research initiative exploring gaming culture in Ghana</p>
            </div>
            
            <div class="ghana-project">
                <h3 class="project-title">Research Initiative</h3>
                <p class="project-text">The "Ghana And Video Games" project is a groundbreaking research initiative exploring the intersection of gaming culture and Ghanaian society. Through comprehensive surveys and community engagement, we're documenting perceptions of video games and game development across Ghana.</p>
                
                <h4 class="project-title">Research Objectives</h4>
                <ul class="project-list">
                    <li>Map the landscape of gaming culture across different demographics in Ghana</li>
                    <li>Identify barriers to entry for aspiring Ghanaian game developers</li>
                    <li>Explore the potential of games as tools for cultural expression and education</li>
                    <li>Assess market opportunities for locally developed games reflecting Ghanaian narratives</li>
                </ul>
                
                <h4 class="project-title">Current Progress</h4>
                <p class="project-text">Our ongoing survey is collecting vital data on gaming habits, technological access, perception of game development as a career, and interest in games that represent local culture. Initial findings suggest significant untapped potential and enthusiasm for game development in Ghana.</p>
                
                <h4 class="project-title">Future Impact</h4>
                <p class="project-text">Based on our research, we aim to develop resources and initiatives to support Ghana's emerging game development ecosystem, including workshops, mentorship programs, and game jams focused on creating experiences that showcase Ghanaian heritage.</p>
                
                <div class="project-cta">
                    <a href="#" class="btn">Participate in Survey</a>
                    <a href="#" class="game-link secondary-link">View Research Progress</a>
                </div>
            </div>
